Description: LocationLogic provides platform software, applications frameworks, and professional services to wireless services distributors.
Headquarters Regions: Midwestern US
Full Description: As of May 19, 2009, LocationLogic LLC was acquired by TeleCommunication Systems Inc. LocationLogic LLC provides platform software, applications frameworks, and professional services to wireless services providers. It offers LocationLogic software platform that provides the infrastructure, application services, content provisioning, and integration services, as well as the network connectivity, location-enabling services, and tools for deploying and maintaining location-based services, and offers the processing of transaction volumes, integration with existing network infrastructure, and an environment for developing new applications. The company also provides LocationLogic Insight, a software and an on-demand mobile resource management solution for small businesses; and LocationLogic Family Minder, a product suite for promoting communication within the family circle; a location gateway that manages application access to subscriber location information; a suite of geo-services for delivering location-based services; and professional services, such as installation, integration, and consulting services, as well as marketing programs, including marketing support services for activation, usage, and retention. Its LocationLogic software combines a wireless subscriber's location with relevant information; refines and analyzes location information; manages data sets; provides a content management framework for developers to integrate and access spatial data sets; supports open standards that provide integration with existing applications; integrates with various network applications; provides an integration point to the carrier's current location determination infrastructure; and supports application programming interface for building location-based services.  The company is based in Overland Park, Kansas.

Description: Socially powered niche marketplaces
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: pedalr is a many to many marketplace platform initially designed for the billion dollar plus cycling enthusiast marketplace. It is designed for the millions of cyclists, local retailers, and small and large manufacturers around the world who are constantly creating, buying and selling, new and used bicycles, parts, accessories and gear. Our platform solves the problem of no existing single marketplace for individuals, retailers, and small and large brands to buy and sell their new and used items, and create brand awareness in a single common persistent marketplace of like minded buyers and sellers. The  platform is designed to connect buyers and sellers in a community of liked minded cycling enthusiasts which is local, national and international in scope. We are particularly interested in the opportunity presented by operating at the nexus of the transaction between buyers and sellers, in a community of passionate users. The platform does not take the place of existing social networks rather it leverages all the current existing hooks which allow users to create accounts using their existing social profiles and get viral distribution back out through these social networks. While initially focused on the passionate cycling enthusiast marketplace, the pedalr platform is by design one that can be easily ported to other verticals creating a nearly limitless market for processing the transaction and subscription SaaS opportunities. pedalr derives income from a percentage of each sale, premium accounts and placements, strategic partnerships with local and national brands, traditional advertisement, and ultimately software as a service.

Full Description: We strive to help our clients realize their unique definition of success. To achieve this, our team provides a comprehensive service offering aimed at supporting lower middle market business owners at nearly all stages of their company’s lifecycle. Our team has supported over 2,000 clients since 2002 and completed more than 1,150 transactions. This experience, coupled with our history as founders, owners and operators ourselves provides our team with an unparalleled practical knowledge base and real world perspective that is aligned with our clients. When we provide mergers & acquisitions advisory services, explore capital sourcing and deployment options, evaluate valuation drivers or structure a realistic exit plan, we do so knowing that our clients rely on us to help manage what may be their largest asset and the culmination of years of extraordinary efforts. If our client has an interim leadership need, we approach the assignment as if it were our business, reputation, investment and our future retirement at stake – because ultimately it is. The value we provide and the quality of our efforts will make or break a successful engagement. In doing so we are not only able to capitalize on each of our management experiences, but we are also able to draw from best practices learned from working with thousands of clients across all industry sectors. As a result our perspective is broad and our resource base is vast. Our full service approach supports the notion that your business is more than just a transaction to you and us, it’s our business too. Your success translates into our success, just as we shoulder the burden of any failure. As a result we consider ourselves to not only be our client’s solutions advisor, but also their partner.
Industry Groups: Financial Services, Lending and Investments, Real Estate
